    "text": "April 8th, 2015, was significant for several reasons. On that day, \"Lost\" fans celebrated the alignment of 4:23.42 pm, which has been associated with the show. Additionally, it was also \"Rex Manning Day,\" as Twitter paid tribute to the character Rex Manning from the film \"Empire Records\". Other dates that are notable due to films include April 14th, known as \"Titanic Day\", and October 3rd, celebrated as \"Mean Girls Day\". October 21st, 2015, is recognized as the date when Marty McFly traveled to in \"Back to the Future Part II\".",
